<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Twin1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Twin,</orth> one of two children born at a birth: <cit><quote>the t. Dromio,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.350" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 350</bibl></cit>. Plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 56</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.10.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 10, 12</bibl>. <cit><quote>t. brother,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O hard condition, twin-born with greatness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.251" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 251</bibl></cit>.<lb />Adjectively, == perfectly resembling: <cit><quote>an apple, cleft in two, is not more t. than these two creatures,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.230" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 230</bibl></cit>. Perhaps also in <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>